We all have problems and in this life time most men go through life with an empty emotional bank account and mainly because society has it's weight pressing too hard on them. Self-help books are books that are written with the intention to instruct its readers on solving personal problems. The books take their name from Self-Help, an 1859 best-seller by Samuel Smiles, but are also known and classified under "self-improvement", a term that is a modernized version of self-help. Self-help books moved from a niche position to being a postmodern cultural phenomenon in the late twentieth century. These books provide informal guides to everyday behaviour with the possibilities of changing it to good behavior. These 10 books might help you Get a perspective on your life: 1) As A Man Thinketh By James Allen 2) Awaken The Giant Within By Tony Robbins 3) Getting Things Done By David Allen 4) How To Stop Worrying And Start Living By Dale Carnegie 5) Making A Good Brain Great By Daniel G Amen 6) Man’s Search For Meaning By Viktor E Frankl 7) Outliers By Malcolm Gladwell 8) The 33 Strategies Of War By Robert Greene 9) 7 Habits Of Highly Effective People By Stephen Covey10) The Millionaire Next Door By Thomas Stanley And William Danko